Review: I enjoyed this way more than I thought I would. The story is somewhat predictable, I'm sure I've seen movies with a similar dynamic and plot points before but the two leads are so incredibly well done. Every interaction was just so heartfelt and they just felt so, so human. Loved it. Adore River Phoenix of course.

Review: A bit of a middle of the road movie for me. I wasn't particularly involved in the characters but it had some decent action scenes and I did really like how it played out in a fairly small space, seeing the apartments get taken over really added to the feeling of being trapped. I have very low demands for zombie movies tbh so I'd say this one delivered.

Movie: The Kid Who Would Be King

Review: My first trip to the cinema since the beginning of you-know-what. I enjoyed this overall, I was completely alone in the room (and the whole tiny cinema in my town) and I'm pretty easily spooked so overall it was a pretty good experience. Anya Taylor-Joy was a stand-out of course.I guess it lacked the humour that I love from the Cornetto-triology and it wasn't such a stand-out as a thriller so maybe there were some lost opportunities on that front but other than that I liked it for what it was.

Instantly became one of my modern Disney favourites. Even though Disney has its usual tropes and character types this felt so fresh and was so much fun. It was emotional and had a message without being heavy-handed and its use of modern references and language wasn’t cringey at all. I really liked this all the way through and it goes without saying that the animation was great.
